      "id": 358786,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Galactose, one of the eight essential monosaccharides (<b>Section 25.7</b>), is biosynthesized from UDP-glucose by galactose 4-epimerase, where UDP = uridylyl diphosphate (a ribonucleotide diphosphate; <b>Section 28.1</b>). The enzyme requires NAD<sup>+</sup> for activity (<b>Section 17.7</b>), but it is not a stoichiometric reactant, and NADH is not a final reaction product. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbjBaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--0e7effb7c4648bb8c529985fe2b1c659a8c821a6/OChem_25_EC_006.jpg\" alt=\"U D P galactose is converted by a N A D cation to U D P-galactose.\">",
